---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import avatar from '../assets/nishat.png';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="I'm Nishat. I write about WordPress SaaS marketing, systems thinking, and what it actually takes to grow a product team from the inside." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-header">
				<Image src={avatar} alt="Nishat Shahriyar" class="avatar" width={120} height={120} />
				<h1>About</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="prose">
				<p>
					I'm Nishat Shahriyar. I write about WordPress SaaS marketing, systems thinking, and what it actually
					takes to grow a product team from the inside.
				</p>

				<p>
					For the past five years I've worked at <a href="https://wpmanageninja.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WPManageNinja</a>,
					the company behind Fluent Forms, Ninja Tables, Fluent Support, FluentCommunity, FluentCart,
					FluentPlayer, Paymattic, and FluentBooking. I started as a content writer in 2021, moved into
					SEO content strategy, then led a content team and ran marketing for Fluent Support (10K users).
					Now I own marketing for Fluent Forms (700K users), Ninja Tables (80K users), and FluentPlayer
					(newly launched) — running content, SEO, lifecycle email, and AI-augmented workflows for a
					five-person team.
				</p>

				<p>
					That's the day job. This blog is where I write down what I've actually learned doing it: the
					systems, the mistakes, the stuff that worked because it was boring and repeatable, not because
					it was clever.
				</p>

				<p>
					I'm also active in the WordPress community. I run 3 newsletters: <a href="https://wpmore.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> WP More</a> for WordPress & WP community news, 
				    <a href="https://serplabseo.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> SERPLabSEO</a> for SEO and marketing updates,
					a personal curated one on tech, ceator economy, pop culture and business at <a href="https://nishishere.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nishishere.com</a>,
					and a blog <a href="https://nishnama.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nishnama</a>, where I write in
					Bangla, my native language.
				</p>

				<p>
					Most of what shows up here sits at the intersection of WordPress, SEO, AI-augmented content
					systems, and personal branding — partly because that's my job, and partly because most
					marketing advice for SaaS companies skips the operational layer that actually makes it work.
				</p>

				<p>
					This blog also doubles as a journal — thoughts and opinions on life, marriage, raising a kid,
					work, and whatever else I find interesting at the time.
				</p>

				<p>
					Short version: I build content systems for WordPress products, and I'm trying to get better
					at explaining how, in public.
				</p>

				<div class="social">
					<span class="social-label">Follow me</span>
					<a href="https://twitter.com/rednishat" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X</a>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nishatshahriyar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
	}

	.avatar {
		width: 80px;
		height: 80px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		object-fit: cover;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.prose {
		max-width: 600px;
	}

	.prose p {
		margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.prose a {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 3px;
	}

	.prose a:hover {
		color: var(--accent-hover);
	}

	.social {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		padding-top: 1.5rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.social-label {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-right: 0.25rem;
	}

	.social a {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 999px;
		transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
	}

	.social a:hover {
		color: var(--accent);
		border-color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: none;
	}
</style>
